### Q1. Install a Text Editor or Integrated Development Environment (IDE): Select and install a text editor or IDE suitable for your programming languages and workflow. Download and Install Visual Studio Code. https://code.visualstudio.com/Download
## VSCODE INSTALLATION GUIDE
Visual Studio Code (VS Code) is a lightweight but powerful source code editor developed by
Microsoft. It's designed to be highly customizable and extensible, catering to a wide range of
programming languages and development workflows.Visual Studio Code has a high productivity code editor which, when combined with programming language services, gives you the power of an IDE and the speed of a text editor.
Vscode has many interesting features that makes it one of the most useful and probably easy to use text editor. Below are some of the features associated with vscode:
a)	Cross platform: VS Code is a free code editor, which runs on the macOS, Linux, and Windows operating systems. Vscode is also  lightweight as we have mentioned above,  and should run on most available hardware and platform versions.
b)	Language Support: It offers built-in support for numerous programming languages like JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, Java, C++, and many more. Additionally, you can install extensions to enhance support for specific languages.
c)	IntelliSense: VS Code provides intelligent code completion, syntax highlighting, and code suggestions, helping you write code faster and with fewer errors.
d)	Integrated Terminal: It comes with a built-in terminal, allowing you to run commands, compile code, and perform other tasks without leaving the editor.
e)	Debugger: VS Code includes a debugger for various languages, enabling you to debug your code directly within the editor.
f)	Version Control: It offers built-in Git integration, allowing you to perform version control operations such as committing, pulling, pushing, and resolving merge conflicts without switching to a separate Git client.
g)	Extensions: VS Code's functionality can be extended through a vast ecosystem of extensions available in the Visual Studio Code Marketplace. These extensions add support for new languages, provide additional tools, and enhance your overall development experience.

h)	Customization: You can personalize almost every aspect of VS Code to suit your preferences. This includes themes, keyboard shortcuts, settings, and more.

## VSCODE SETUP AND CONFIGURATIONS
Since I am using a windows 10 OS, let me show you how to install and configure the text editor on my machine. The steps are as follows”
•	First, Download the Vscode installer by visiting their official Visual Studio Code website (https://code.visualstudio.com/) using your web browser. Click on the "Download for Windows" button to download the installer file.
•	Installer: Once the download is complete, locate the downloaded installer file (usually in your Downloads folder as VSCodeUserSetup-{version}.exe) and double-click on it to run it. It will take a few minutes to run the wizard installer 
 











 








 

.You can choose the installation location and whether to add VS Code to your PATH (environment variables) during the installation process

 
 

•	The Visual Studio Code installer will create an icon in the start Menu. To locate it, click on the Start Menu and search for 'vsCode':
NB: 1. VS Code provides both Windows user and system level setups.

The user setup does not require Administrator privileges to run as the location will be under your user Local AppData (LOCALAPPDATA) folder. Since it requires no elevation, the user setup is able to provide a smoother background update experience. This is the preferred way to install VS Code on Windows.
2. The system setup requires elevation to Administrator privileges to run and will place the installation under the system's Program Files. The in-product update flow will also require elevation, making it less streamlined than the user setup. On the other hand, installing VS Code using the system setup means that it will be available to all users in the system.

And that is how you successfully install vscode on a windows machine. You can now add extensions depending on your needs.
### Q2.  Set Up Version Control System: Install Git and configure it on your local machine. Create a GitHub account for hosting your repositories. Initialize a Git repository for your project and make your first commit. https://github.com
First of all let’s define version control system(vcs). Version control, also known as source control, is the practice of tracking and managing changes to software code. Version control systems are software tools that help software teams manage changes to source code over time. As development environments have accelerated, version control systems help software teams work faster and smarter. They are especially useful for DevOps teams since they help them to reduce development time and increase successful deployments.
We have several industry approved vcs’s such as Apache subversion, Mercurial, Perfoce, Git just to mention a few. I am going to show you how to download, install and configure Git as this is the most common used vcs.
## GIT INSTALLATION AND GUIDE
What is Git?
Git is a distributed version control system that tracks versions of files. It is often used to control source code by programmers collaboratively developing software. Git thinks of its data more like a series of snapshots of a miniature filesystem. With Git, every time you commit, or save the state of your project, Git basically takes a picture of what all your files look like at that moment and stores a reference to that snapshot. To be efficient, if files have not changed, Git doesn’t store the file again, just a link to the previous identical file it has already stored. Git thinks about its data more like a stream of snapshots.
. Git has three main states that your files can reside in: modified, staged, and committed:
•	Modified means that you have changed the file but have not committed it to your database yet.
•	Staged means that you have marked a modified file in its current version to go into your next commit snapshot.
•	Committed means that the data is safely stored in your local database.


## GIT SETUP

a)	First, download git for windows on your browser by using the  link:  https://git-scm.com/download/win and the download will start automatically.
b)	Then follow the installation wizard as depicted on the pictorial representations below

 
 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

