•	Before using your git, you first need to configure a few parameters such as user-name, default branch and email as follows:
NB: We interact with git using Git bash IDE. So, open Gitbash and run it as administrator  to have the root privileges that come along with the Git



 

 

 

 

There are a few commands that are imperative to interacting with Git such as 
	git init  - for initializing a repository
	git status  - to know the status of your repositor
	git add “filename” – to track a file or adding that to the staged environment
	git commit -m “message”  - commiting files to the repository
	git log – to show all the commits made

That is how you setup and configure git on your windows pc
