### Q4. Configure a Database (MySQL): Download and install MySQL database.
Mysql is a platform that lets you create databases for your project. A complete mysql set up consists of a mysql client where the user interacts with the mysql server which serves as the key component in storing, retrieving and managing data. The following steps will guide you on how to install and configure  mysql on your pc:
•	The first step is to download Mysql server using the link: https://dev.msql.com/downloads.installer/
•	After download is complete, begin the installation process by locating where the download file is and double click on it
•	Now follow on the installation wizard. On “choosing set up” select “server only” as we need the server first so as to interact with the client.

 

•	 
 
•	On type and networking  make sure you select “Development computer” and select a port number. By default we always use “3306”as the default port. Make sure you also click on “show advanced and logging options” to unhide the other essential steps.
 





•	On the authentication method, click on the recommended option that allows you the user to always use a password whenever you are using mysql
 
•	On windows service check the appropriate boxes and leave everything as it is. You can configure the windows service name to any that you see fit
 




•	On “server file permission” check the first option 
 
•	On logging options configure your username as you want it to appear on your mysql command line
 





•	On advanced options let server ID be as default and check the first option under “Table names
 
•	Ëxecute and let it run for a few minutes
 

 

 
Now that we are done with the installation wizard , the next step is to initiate Mysql server for the first time in your pc. To do that, run CMD as an administrator to and type”
“C:\Program Files \MySQL \MySQL Server 8.0 \bin \mysqld” –console
Once this command is complete we now have Mysql server running. So the next step is to install Mysql workbench from Microsoft. This is the environment a user interacts it when querrying requests from the Mysql server.
